g in a feminist classroom; and a description of the controversy that resulted when the author refused to allow a hostile male student to take one of her courses. Beautifully written,The Family Silver addresses issues of central concern to feminists, postmodernists, and queer theorists and encourages new insights into how gender profoundly affects us all.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aFeminist theoryxUnited States. 0aFeminist theoryzUnited States. 0aGender identityxUnited States. 0aGender identityzUnited States. 0aInterpersonal relationsxUnited States. 0aInterpersonal relationszUnited States. 0aLesbiansxUnited States. 0aLesbianszUnited States. 0aWomen college teachersxUnited States. 0aWomen college teacherszUnited States. 0aWomenxUnited States. 0aWomenzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aacademia.  aacademic.  aanalysis.  acontroversial.  adomestic.  aemotions.  aessay collection.  afamily life.  afemale teachers.  afeminism.  afeminist studies.  afeminist.  agender expression.  agender roles.  agender studies.  agender.  ainterpersonal relationships.  alesbians.  algbtq.  amaterial wealth.  amental health.  amother daughter.  apostmodern.  aqueer theory.  aresearch.  ascholarly.  astrong women.  ateaching.  awealth.  awomens issues.  awomens studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052091705740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520917057423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520917057/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles